; 1861-1916: Pierre Duhem

* Scientific hypotheses only work given further auxiliary hypotheses, some of which are about the experimental equipment.
* Observations and experiments cannot be by themselves decisive in refuting scientific hypotheses.
* When a prediction fails, the scientist may reconsider the theoretical postulates or check the equipment.